
TY  - JOUR
T1  - Organizational Goals and Expected Behavior among American, Japanese and Korean Managers—A Comparative Study
AU  - England, George W.
AU  - Lee, Raymond
Y1  - 1971/12/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/12/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255058
DO  - 10.5465/255058
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 425
EP  - 438
VL  - 14
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Empirical evidence is presented about organizational goals as viewed by samples of over 1,600 American, Japanese, and Korean managers. Comparative analyses of organizational goal perceptions and expected organizational behavior suggest that cultural factors have an important impact on managerial values as expressed in organizational goals. Country differences and similarities found in the perceptions of goals are generally in accord with the managerial ideology, economic development, and social facts of the three countries.
AB  - Empirical evidence is presented about organizational goals as viewed by samples of over 1,600 American, Japanese, and Korean managers. Comparative analyses of organizational goal perceptions and expected organizational behavior suggest that cultural factors have an important impact on managerial values as expressed in organizational goals. Country differences and similarities found in the perceptions of goals are generally in accord with the managerial ideology, economic development, and social facts of the three countries.
SN  - 0001-4273
