N2  - The article reports the author's opinions regarding the social status of the managers of business enterprises. He focuses on the occupational tasks associated with the position of manager and whether or not managers can be considered professionals. It is suggested that a key component of professionalism is an individual's inherent value for his or her profession. The implications of obtaining a Master of Business Administration degree are also discussed.
